Lolium rigidum

   [1363.jpg]
    Authority   Gaudin
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names Wimmera ryegrass
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 1363

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A grass with ascending, spreading smooth and glabrous
   rather stout stems, reaching up to 80 cm in height and often branched
   at the base. USES The grass is palatable to livestock especially during
   the vegetative stage, when the grass is young and succulent. KILLING T
   Seedlings may resist -3 to -4Â°C for short periods. GROWING PERIOD
   Annual grass. COMMON NAMES Rigid ryegrass, Annual ryegrass, Swiss
   ryegrass, Wimmera ryegrass, C'hortam, Samma, Zaywahn, Sahleh, Zommeir,
   Sammah,
   Nusayl, El-shailem, Ruwaita, Irwaita, Hamaita. FURTHER INF Scientific
   synonym: L. strictum. Rigid ryegrass is common in the Mediterranean
   region. In Tunisia it can be found at elevations between 300-1200 m and
   in Iran and Irak up to 3500 m.

   Sources
   SOURCES (L. rigidum Gaud.)
   Kernick M 1978 pp 375-397 [DRA, RAIN, TEMP, KTMP, TEXT, USE]
   Kernick M 1961 pp 38 [PHO]

